<TITLE> 7 of a wedding party die in Bogra bus crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, Dec 11 (bdnews24.com)  Seven persons were killed when a microbus carrying a wedding party was hit by a passenger bus near Shivganj bus stand in Bogra on Thursday. The microbus, on its way to Sherpur, was hit by the bus as it reached Shivganj. The seven died on the spot, said police. The dead have been identified as Bulbuli (23), China (40), Zahura (22), Rafiq (10), Rafiq Kazi (5), Zahid (4) and microbus driver Omar Faruk (30). Two injured passengers, the bridegroom Zakiru (20) and elder brother Zahirul (26) were admitted to hospital. The bus driver and his assistant managed to flee the scene, though locals ran after the bus and stopped it. Efforts are underway to lodge a case in this regard, police said.. bdnews24.com/cor
